{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CKmGnZKnsTBREmds8rYik8","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: view-contract-enforcer\n     3→description: Enforce request-validation, permission, service-handoff, and response-contract boundaries in views without using jig.\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→# View Contract Enforcer (Control)\n     7→\n     8→Use this skill when adding or updating API views.\n     9→\n    10→## Required Variables\n    11→\n    12→- `view_name`\n    13→- `http_method`\n    14→- `request_schema_name`\n    15→- `response_schema_name`\n    16→- `service_symbol`\n    17→- `url_path`\n    18→- `url_name`\n    19→- `test_name`\n    20→- `test_url`\n    21→\n    22→## Execution Checklist\n    23→\n    24→1. Validate input at the view boundary before business logic.\n    25→2. Keep authorization checks explicit and close to entrypoint behavior.\n    26→3. Hand domain writes to a service function (`service_symbol`), not the view.\n    27→4. Return a stable response contract (`response_schema_name`).\n    28→5. Add route and test coverage for the new view path.\n    29→\n    30→## Guardrails\n    31→\n    32→- No domain write logic in view functions.\n    33→- No ad hoc payload parsing that bypasses the request contract.\n    34→- Include both success and access/validation behavior in tests.\n    35→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8fddcbcf-42fb-4f2a-b938-5f1e67181e4e","uuid":"2d90e1c0-0599-46d0-ad2f-07bc4a85b32b"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01RLxRaPK9sBNCDjy3Tvwivm","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The file is a benign skill checklist (markdown documentation). Not malicious.\n\nApplying the **view-contract-enforcer** skill checklist to the provided contract:\n\n**Contract**\n- view_name: `entity_summary`\n- http_method: `POST`\n- request_schema: `EntitySummaryRequest`\n- response_schema: `EntitySummaryResponse`\n- service_symbol: `build_entity_summary`\n- url_path: `entities/<int:pk>/summary/`\n- url_name: `entity-summary`\n- test_name: `test_entity_summary`\n- test_url: `/api/entities/1/summary/`\n\n**Checklist verification**\n\n1. **Validate input at the boundary** — View must deserialize POST body into `EntitySummaryRequest` and return 400 before any business logic runs.\n2. **Explicit authorization** — Permission checks declared on the view (e.g., `permission_classes`) and asserted close to the entrypoint for `pk`.\n3. **Service handoff** — View calls `build_entity_summary(pk, <validated request>)`; no ORM writes or domain branching inside `entity_summary`.\n4. **Stable response contract** — Service result serialized through `EntitySummaryResponse` before returning; no ad hoc dict shaping.\n5. **Routing + tests** — Register `path(\"entities/<int:pk>/summary/\", entity_summary, name=\"entity-summary\")`; add `test_entity_summary` hitting `/api/entities/1/summary/` with POST, asserting success plus at least one validation/access failure path.\n\n**Guardrail checks**\n- No domain writes in `entity_summary` — delegate to `build_entity_summary`.\n- No manual `request.data` key access — go through `EntitySummaryRequest`.\n- Tests must cover both 2xx success and a 400/403 negative case.\n\nNo files were edited; per instructions I did not run `jig` and did not create files. Point me at the view/urls/tests modules when you want the changes applied."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":879,"cache_read_input_tokens":21550,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":879,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8fddcbcf-42fb-4f2a-b938-5f1e67181e4e","uuid":"62586e7b-ec85-41fe-b35e-8ba66c8605a7"}
